ax refers to the distance of the load’s center of mass from the elbow along the arm’s longitudinal axis; y refers to the orthogonal distance of the load’s center of mass from the arm’s longitudinal axis, where a positive (negative) distance indicates a position on the radial (ulnar) side of the forearm
bΔe3 indicates the angle between the smallest eigenvector (e3) of the left and the right forearm. A positive angle indicates that e3 of the right forearm was manipulated towards elbow flexion and e3 of the left forearm towards elbow extension
cΔCM indicates the angle between the center of mass vector (CM) of the left and the right forearm. A positive angle indicates that CM of the right forearm was oriented towards elbow flexion and CM of the left forearm towards elbow extension
